tr.th: Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us

tr.td: The patient shows elevated blood glucose and creatinine, suggesting possible diabetes and impaired renal function. Cholesterol is slightly above normal, indicating increased cardiovascular risk. All other parameters, including electrolytes, liver enzymes (except mildly low AST), and proteins, are within normal limits. Recommend further evaluation of renal function and glycemic control.
